waiting at the agreed spot.

294
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,520
Bribing a single conductor

295
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:27,880
can give you control
over an entire transportation line,

296
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:30,800
bypassing all the checks

297
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:31,960
on the platform and the train.

298
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:35,640
What a good deal.

299
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:39,560
Were they transporting ecstasy or meth?

300
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:41,640
Ecstasy.

301
00:16:41,680 --> 00:16:42,640
Just ecstasy?

302
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:44,000
Never transported meth?

303
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:48,600
But I once heard Liang complain.

304
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:51,720
He said people in Halan
had expanded their business.

305
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:53,000
They ditched ecstasy

306
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,320
for meth

307
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,400
since it's more profitable.

308
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,840
Did they ever mention

309
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,280
who's handling the pickup in Halan?

310
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,640
I've only heard Liang mention it once.

311
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:07,680
A Yuedong guy was
responsible for transporting goods.

312
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:10,280
Later on, he ran away with the goods.

313
00:17:11,120 --> 00:17:12,040
The buyer in Halan

314
